# HCC bcftools Variant Calling Pipeline  
**(Parallel chunked processing per chromosome group)**

Lightweight PBS-based workflow for joint variant calling on human whole-genome sequencing data using **bcftools mpileup → call → annotate → filter**.

Designed for shared HPC environments where each person/user is assigned a small group of chromosomes (e.g. chr1 + chr14 + chr21) and processes only those chromosomes.

## Features

- Fixed-size genomic chunking (default: 10 Mbp)
- Automatic skip of already completed chunks (via checkpoint files)
- Parallel processing of up to 3 chromosomes inside one 24-core SMP node
- Each chromosome uses 8 threads
- Special ploidy handling for chrM and chrY (haploid calling)
- dbsnp annotation (ID field)
- Basic QUAL-based filtering (≥20)
- Detailed per-region timing + status logs
- Easy resume after job interruption
- Final per-chromosome VCFs (compressed & indexed)

## Directory Layout (per chromosome group)
group_runs/
└── chr1_chr14_chr21/                 # CHROM_GROUP_TAG
├── regions.tsv                   # generated by 01_make_regions.sh
├── master_logs/
├── chunks/
│   ├── chr1/
│   │   ├── HCC.chr1.1_10000000.bcf
│   │   ├── HCC.chr1.1_10000000.annotated.bcf
│   │   └── HCC.chr1.1_10000000.filtered.vcf.gz
│   ├── chr14/
│   └── chr21/
├── logs/           # detailed per-chunk logs
├── checkpoints/    # *.done stamp files
├── summaries/      # timing & status TSV files per chunk
└── final/
├── HCC.chr1.bcftools.annotated.filtered.vcf.gz
├── HCC.chr14.bcftools.annotated.filtered.vcf.gz
└── HCC.chr21.bcftools.annotated.filtered.vcf.gz
text## Quick Start – What Each Person Should Do

1. **Edit only one file** — `pipeline.conf`

   ```bash
   CHROM_LIST=(chr1 chr14 chr21)     # ← change this to YOUR assigned chromosomes

Run the pipeline steps in orderBash# 1. Generate regions.tsv (only needed once)
bash run_pipeline.sh setup

# 2. Submit the main parallel chunk processing job (24-core SMP)
bash run_pipeline.sh submit

# ── wait until job finishes ──

# 3. Merge chunked VCFs into one file per chromosome
bash run_pipeline.sh merge
Check progress anytimeBashbash run_pipeline.sh progress→ creates a report in group_runs/<your_group>/progress_report_*.txt

Available Commands
textbash run_pipeline.sh <command>

  setup     →  submit 01_make_regions.sh   (creates regions.tsv)
  submit    →  submit 02_run_chunks.sh     (main parallel variant calling)
  progress  →  submit 04_check_progress.sh (recommended progress report)
  merge     →  submit 03_merge_chromosomes.sh
  help      →  show this help
Resuming / Recovering from Failure

Most common case — just re-runBashbash run_pipeline.sh submit→ already finished chunks are automatically skipped
If many chunks failed midway (partial files exist)Option A — manual cleanup (safer)
Look in logs/chr*/ and summaries/chr*/
Delete only the incomplete files for the failed region(s)
Re-submit
Option B — automatic cleanup of incomplete filesBashqsub -v AUTO_CLEAN_INCOMPLETE=1 02_run_chunks.sh

Configuration (pipeline.conf)

VariableDefault / ExampleMeaningCHROM_LIST(chr1 chr14 chr21)Your assigned chromosomesCHUNK_SIZE10000000Size of each region (bp)MAX_DEPTH1000--max-depth in mpileupPARALLEL_CHROMS3How many chromosomes run concurrentlyTHREADS_PER_CHROM8Threads per chromosome (→ 3×8 = 24)BAM_LIST/path/to/HCC_BAM.txtList of input BAM files (one per line)CONFIG_TXT/path/to/config.txtShared project paths (ref, dbsnp, etc.)
Output Files – Per Chunk

HCC.<chr>.<start>_<end>.bcf
raw multi-sample BCF after mpileup + call
HCC.<chr>.<start>_<end>.annotated.bcf
dbSNP rsIDs

HCC.<chr>.<start>_<end>.filtered.vcf.gz
final output after QUAL ≥ 20 filter

Requirements

PBS Pro scheduler
bcftools ≥ 1.10 (preferably recent version)
bgzip & tabix
Reference genome: hg38.fa + .fai
Input BAMs listed in ${BAM_LIST}
dbsnp file: dbsnp_146.hg38.vcf.gz (or update path)